Lagos Water Corporation (LWC) Managing Director Mr. Muminu Badmus yesterday apologised to residents for interruption in supply. In a statement, he blamed the disruption on epileptic power supply, which affected production. He said: “The corporation is working on alternative power supply to strengthen its operations. “The public should conserve water, save, store and use water wisely, especially during this period.” The statement said residents should trust the corporation for improved service delivery. It said LWC was committed to the provision of uninterrupted potable water. 